Assistant: Sure, I'd be happy to explain Astro in shadcn-vue.

# Astro

Adding dark mode to your astro app.Here's a quick rundown of what this is about:

## Dark mode

Adding dark mode to your astro app.

## Create an inline theme script

```astro
---
import '../styles/globals.css'
---

<script is:inline>
	const getThemePreference = () => {
		if (typeof localStorage !== 'undefined' && localStorage.getItem('theme')) {
			return localStorage.getItem('theme');
		}
		return window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches ? 'dark' : 'light';
	};
	const isDark = getThemePreference() === 'dark';
	document.documentElement.classList[isDark ? 'add' : 'remove']('dark');

	if (typeof localStorage !== 'undefined') {
		const observer = new MutationObserver(() => {
			const isDark = document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark');
			localStorage.setItem('theme', isDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
		});
		observer.observe(document.documentElement, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['class'] });
	}
</script>

<html lang="en">
	<body>
      <h1>Astro</h1>
	</body>
</html>
```

This should give you a solid starting point!

